@c page
@node conf options
@section Options for @command{configure}


For the full list of available configuration options, we should try the
command:

@example
$ ../configure --help
@end example

@noindent
what follows is a list of common options.


@table @code
@item --enable-ikarus
@itemx --enable-ypsilon
@c @itemx --enable-larceny
Enable the usage of a Scheme implementation.

@item --prefix=@var{value}
Select the directory to be used as installation prefix; all the files
installed by a project will end under this directory; it defaults to
@file{/usr/local}.

@item --enable-fasl
@itemx --disable-fasl
Enable or disable the compilation and installation of @fasl{} files;
these are the precompiled version of the installed libraries.  It
defaults to: no, do not precompile files.

At present (revision 1695) only libraries can be compiled by Ikarus.

@item --enable-sls
@itemx --disable-sls
Enable or disable the installation of source files.  It defaults to:
yes, install the source files.

@item --enable-doc
@itemx --disable-doc
Enable or disable the compilation and installation of documentation
files.  It defaults to: yes, build and install the documentation.

@item --enable-doc-info
@itemx --disable-doc-info
Enable or disable the compilation and installation of Info documentation
files.  It defaults to: yes, build and install the Info documentation.

@item --enable-doc-html
@itemx --disable-doc-html
Enable or disable the compilation and installation of @acronym{HTML}
documentation files.  It defaults to: no, @strong{do not} build and
install the @acronym{HTML} documentation.
@end table


