@section Running Ikarus Scheme


@deffn {Autoconf Macro} NAUSICAA_WITH_OUTPUT_FROM_IKARUS_SCRIPT (@var{scheme_code}, @var{options}, @var{shell_chunk})
Evaluate @var{scheme_code} with Ikarus by storing it in a temporary file
and invoking "@code{$@{IKARUS@} --r6rs-script} with additional command
line @var{options}.  Then, after the temporary file has been removed,
evaluate @var{shell_chunk}.

The script is expected to print a line of text on its standard output,
which will be stored in the shell variable @code{nausicaa_ANSWER}, so
that @var{shell_chunk} can examine it.
@end deffn


@deffn {Autoconf Macro} NAUSICAA_IKARUS_CHECK_LIBRARY (@var{name}, @var{import_spec}, @var{action_if_found}, @var{action_if_not_found})
Attempt to find a Scheme library loadable by Ikarus.

If the library is found the output variable
@code{HAS_IKARUS_LIB_@var{name}} is set to @code{yes}, otherwise it is
set to @code{no}.

The optional @var{action_if_found} is executed if the library was found.
The optional @var{action_if_not_found} is executed if the library was
not found.
@end deffn


As an example, here is the implementation of the macro above:

@example
AC_DEFUN([NAUSICAA_IKARUS_CHECK_LIBRARY],[
AC_MSG_CHECKING([availability of Ikarus library $2])
NAUSICAA_WITH_OUTPUT_FROM_IKARUS_SCRIPT([(import (rnrs) (rnrs eval (6)))
(with-exception-handler
  (lambda (ex)
    (display "no\n")
    (exit))
  (lambda ()
    (environment (quote $2))
    (display "yes\n")))
],,[if test "$nausicaa_ANSWER" = yes ; then
: dnl action if found.
$3
else
: dnl action if not found.
$4
fi
AC_MSG_RESULT([$nausicaa_ANSWER])
AC_SUBST([HAS_IKARUS_LIB_$1],[$nausicaa_ANSWER])
])
])
@end example

@noindent
and here is how we verify if @library{uriel ffi} is installed:

@example
NAUSICAA_IKARUS_CHECK_LIBRARY([URIEL_FFI],[(uriel ffi)])
@end example


